    "# Use Case #5: Human-in-the-Loop Decision & Approval Systems with LangGraph\n",
    "\n",
    "## How BigCompany Inc. Keeps Humans in Control of High-Stakes AI Decisions\n",
    "\n",
    "**The key to putting AI agents in production safely — solving the #1 barrier to enterprise AI adoption.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## The Problem: BigCompany Inc. Needs AI, But Can't Afford Mistakes\n",
    "\n",
    "**BigCompany Inc.** is a growing software company with 500 employees. Their **Finance department** processes hundreds of expense reports every week — employees submit expenses for travel, software subscriptions, office supplies, and client dinners.\n",
    "\n",
    "The current process is painful:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Each expense report must be **manually reviewed** by a finance manager.\n",
    "- The manager checks the category, amount, and company policy compliance.\n",
    "- **Small expenses** (under 500 dollars) are routine — they almost always get approved.\n",
    "- **Large expenses** (over 500 dollars) need careful review — they sometimes violate company policy or need budget verification.\n",
    "- The finance team spends **20 hours per week** just reviewing and approving expenses.\n",
    "- Employees wait **3-5 business days** for reimbursement.\n",
    "\n",
    "The CFO has an idea:\n",
    "\n",
    "> *\"What if AI could handle the routine expense approvals automatically, but still ask a human manager to approve the big or unusual ones? We'd save time AND keep control over important decisions.\"*\n",
    "\n",
    "This is the perfect use case for **Human-in-the-Loop (HITL)** — a pattern where AI handles the routine work, but **pauses and asks a human** before making high-stakes decisions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Why Human-in-the-Loop Matters\n",
    "\n",
    "According to the [State of AI Agent Engineering Report](https://www.langchain.com/state-of-agent-engineering) (surveying 1,340+ professionals), the **#1 barrier** to putting AI agents in production is **quality concerns** — 32% of respondents worry about AI making mistakes on important decisions.\n",
    "\n",
    "Human-in-the-loop solves this problem by creating **checkpoints** where a human must approve before the AI continues:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Scenario | Without HITL | With HITL |\n",
    "|----------|-------------|----------|\n",
    "| AI approves a $10,000 expense that violates policy | Money is lost | Human catches the error before approval |\n",
    "| AI misclassifies an expense category | Wrong budget is charged | Human corrects the category |\n",
    "| AI processes a duplicate expense | Employee gets paid twice | Human spots the duplicate |\n",
    "\n",
    "The key insight: **AI does 90% of the work; humans provide the 10% that requires judgment.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## How Does Human-in-the-Loop Work in LangGraph?\n",
    "\n",
    "LangGraph provides a powerful function called **`interrupt()`** that makes HITL easy:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **The agent works autonomously** — classifying expenses, checking policy, calculating totals.\n",
    "2. **At a critical decision point**, the agent calls `interrupt()` — execution **pauses** and a message is shown to the human.\n",
    "3. **The human reviews** and responds — approve, reject, or edit.\n",
    "4. **The agent resumes** from exactly where it paused — using `Command(resume=...)` to pass the human's decision back.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Agent works on task...\n",
    "        │\n",
    "        ▼\n",
    "┌─────────────────┐\n",
    "│  interrupt()    │ ◄── Agent pauses here\n",
    "│  \"Approve this  │     and asks the human\n",
    "│   $2,000        │\n",
    "│   expense?\"     │\n",
    "└────────┬────────┘\n",
    "         │\n",
    "    Human reviews\n",
    "    and responds\n",
    "         │\n",
    "         ▼\n",
    "┌─────────────────┐\n",
    "│ Command(resume= │ ◄── Human's decision\n",
    "│  \"approved\")    │     is passed back\n",
    "└────────┬────────┘\n",
    "         │\n",
    "         ▼\n",
    "Agent continues...\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why This Is Technically Impressive\n",
    "\n",
    "When the agent pauses, it might wait **minutes, hours, or even days** for a human response. LangGraph handles this through its **checkpointing system**:\n",
    "\n",
    "- The entire graph state is **saved automatically** when `interrupt()` is called.\n",
    "- The paused agent uses **zero compute resources** — it's just data in storage.\n",
    "- When the human responds, the agent **resumes exactly where it left off** — no lost context, no restarting.\n",
    "- In production, a `PostgresSaver` stores state in a database, so the agent survives server restarts."
   ]
  },
